### Style Profile — EIW Line

His OIS illustration establishes a clear aesthetic:
warm palette, storybook atmosphere, literary weight.
Landscape illustration featuring a castle, geese, and a winding road —
multiple collections built from crops of a single piece.
His portrait of Evan: black and white, painterly, Hemingway-inspired —
sketched and lived-in, his distinct hand unmistakably present.
Font pairing: Oldbook ITC — literary, ornamental, timeless.

His illustration style is the EIW visual identity.
It is not pixel art and does not translate to pixel art —
a cross-style experiment with Marwan confirmed this (see below).
Luiz lives in his own lane. That lane is the right lane for EIW.

### What Luiz Is Not Designing

The Outside Inn lo-fi / pixel art aesthetic (Marwan's territory)
exists on the same YouTube channel and Fourthwall store.
Luiz knows it exists but is not designing for it.
These two aesthetics intentionally diverge — accepted for v1.

