## Creative Scope — EIW Line (Full Reference)

Luiz is the visual artist for the EIW brand line only.
This is the full scope of his design responsibility.

### 1. Live Stream Overlays

- **Purpose:** Frame Evan's facecam + screen share without cluttering content
- **Platform targets:** YouTube Live + Twitch simultaneously
- **Canvas:** 1920×1080, PNG with transparency
- **Facecam window:** 480×270px, bottom-left or bottom-right (placement to be tested)
- **Scenes:** Writing Stream (facecam + Notion) and Gaming Stream (facecam + game capture)
- **Aesthetic:** EIW — black and white, painterly, literary
- **Design direction:** Hand-drawn or painterly edges, not geometric perfection.
  Could reference book borders, manuscript margins, inn window frames,
  illustrated chapter headers, old portrait frames.
  Subtle brand presence — E.I. Werner name or Outside Inn mark integrated naturally.
- **Constraint:** Do not obscure more than ~15% of the screen.
  The content is the main event — the overlay supports it.

### 2. Video Overlays (Edited YouTube VODs)

- **Purpose:** Lower thirds, intros, outros for edited uploads (not live)
- **Aesthetic:** EIW — should feel like a literary journal, not a gaming channel
- **Deliverable:** Layered source files + export-ready assets

### 3. Evan's Portrait — Profile Picture

Already completed (in painterly B&W style).
Export and test before finalizing.
- **Size:** 800×800px minimum (export large — platforms display small but store bigger)
- **Format:** PNG
- **Shape:** YouTube crops to circle — face centered, nothing critical near edges
- **Test:** Render at ~98px to confirm face reads at thumbnail scale
- **Test against:** Both light and dark backgrounds (multiple platform contexts)
- **Twitch:** Same rules — confirm whether a separate version is needed

### 4. YouTube Thumbnails

- **Size:** 1280×720px (16:9), minimum 640px wide
- **Format:** JPG or PNG — under 2MB
- **Aesthetic:** EIW only — black and white, painterly, high contrast.
  Should stop the scroll and feel like a literary event.
- **No wordmarks in the art** — text/title overlay added separately
- **Design for legibility at small sizes** (mobile feed) and full desktop
- **Safe zone:** Keep key elements away from edges — YouTube crops in some contexts

### 5. Print Products (EIW Line Only)

All through Fourthwall print-on-demand.

| Product | Final Size | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Classic Mousepad | ~8.5"×7" or 10.5"×8.5" | Confirm exact template |
| Gaming Mousepad (oversized) | ~36"×12" or similar | Confirm exact template |
| Deskmat | **15.5"×31.5"** | Hero product — highest margin (69%) |
| Poster (unframed) | **18"×24"** | Standard art print |
| Poster (framed) | **18"×24"** | Same file — Fourthwall frames it |

**Fourthwall export specs (must follow):**
- Format: PNG only — no TIFF, no PDF
- Minimum resolution: 200 DPI (300 DPI recommended)
- Minimum file size: 5000×5000 pixels
- Color mode: CMYK (not RGB)
- Background: Transparent where possible
- No: semi-transparent elements, glow effects, gradients, fades
- Yes: solid, well-defined shapes with strong outlines
- Mousepads/Deskmats: sublimation printing — PNG, 300 DPI min
- Posters: screen printing or DTG — PNG, 300 DPI min, no gradients for screen print
- Confirm bleed + safe zone per product in Fourthwall dashboard before final export

**Design principle (non-negotiable):**
No wordmarks on any product.
If the design needs words to make sense, the design isn't strong enough.
These pieces should be buyable by someone who doesn't know the brand.
Elevated throughout. This audience has outgrown creator merch.

